From 4a73ae599160b83ef75aa8c50ef70086e87e082e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GloriousEggroll <gloriouseggroll@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 15:58:50 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] winedmo: remove winegstreamer media backend

Move the Proton media-converter, parser, decoder, encoder, sink/source, and Media Foundation glue out of dlls/winegstreamer and into dlls/winedmo.

This starts the rework by deleting the winegstreamer DLL registration and build wiring, adding the winedmo COM classes/spec/rgs entries, and routing the Unix-side demuxer/transform/muxer path through the winedmo Unix library instead of GStreamer.

The replacement keeps the media-converter helpers and Windows Media reader/decoder surfaces available while removing the GStreamer module as a build target.

The winedmo media-type path also replaces the old Metal Gear Solid V / Metal Gear Survive SteamGameId handling for Opus/Vorbis formats by applying sane bits-per-sample defaults generally when FFmpeg reports zero.
